da743205-6ad7-4c24-9bf1-66db66941057.085c8db3-a759-45eb-94b1-98b314eaebf5.description=
Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

Responses\:
success -  The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

Returns\:
The raw result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Returns\:
Field 1 - The first value. Here for compatibility
Field 2 - The second value. Here for compatibility
Field 3 - The operation. Here for compatibility
formatted_result - The formatted result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.
da743205-6ad7-4c24-9bf1-66db66941057.28004a4a-5399-499d-a3ea-8a92a65446f9.description=

da743205-6ad7-4c24-9bf1-66db66941057.58a8c3ba-d3f7-47d8-adc5-c3baaaeec5d9.description=
Sorts a list. If this list is all numerical, it is sorted in numerical order, other wise it is sorted in alphabetical order.

Inputs\:
delimiter - The list delimiter.
list - The list to be processed
reverse - A boolean value, sort the list in reverse order?

Responses\:
success - The operation completed Successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
The sorted list

da743205-6ad7-4c24-9bf1-66db66941057.87534316-ef0b-4b89-ba52-41c6c0093c58.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

da743205-6ad7-4c24-9bf1-66db66941057.d986db63-dd31-45a1-a63e-ac25e6642182.callout=by vServerName da743205-6ad7-4c24-9bf1-66db66941057.description=
Synopsis

    This flow generates a volume name based on the vServer name. The volume name is generated in numeric order.
    generateVolumeName performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve a list of volumes based on the vServer name using the HPOO flow getVolumes.
      2. If no volumes exist, set the new volume name as VOL01 (denoting the first volume in a series).
      3. If volumes exist, sort the list of volume names in alphanumeric order.
      4. Look at the first volume on the list and determine if the net index is greater than or less than nine.
      5. Pass the volume name back to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    vServerName - The name of the vServer to be used in the flow (required).
    siteId - The ID number of the site where the product is located.
    datacenter - The datacenter in which to create the customer's vServer.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow;  {what does this flow return and how is it returned?}  See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
